G-MOE-GPU3-STREAM — GPU residency rung 3: streamed rump experts + threaded recurrence (2026-07-02)
==================================================================================================
BUILT:
1. GDN conv + delta-rule recurrence + gated-norm THREADED (qwen36.c): channels / v-heads are
   independent -> `omp parallel for` with per-head STACK scratch; per-head/channel math order
   unchanged = BIT-EXACT. conv+recur bucket: 0.44s -> 0.11s per 9 steps (4x).
2. STREAMED experts for non-resident layers (cuda_forward.cu): sp_q36gpu_moe_stream ships
   ONLY the selected NU experts' packed slices per token — codes are a CONTIGUOUS byte range
   (row_off ascending absolute), so each slice = ONE H2D + small metadata copies (adjusted
   slab-relative row_off built host-side, row_prec, bscale/row_scale) into a bump-allocated
   device slab (~30MB, reused per call); then the identical per-expert dp4a flow, one sync
   per layer. Harness: host-side table of every layer's expert tensors; the moe hook tries
   resident -> streamed (QWEN36_GPU_STREAM=1) -> CPU.

GATE (35B OK-container, greedy 16, 25 resident + 15 streamed layers):
  SEQ IDENTICAL 21/21 — the seventh arithmetic regime this sequence has survived unchanged
  (scalar, OMP, AVX2, batched, GPU-dense, GPU-resident-experts, GPU-STREAMED-experts).
  VERDICT: **GREEN**.

THE LADDER (16-token greedy, 35B-A3B GDN-MoE, i9-11900KB + RTX 2060 12GB):
  stateless O(n^2)        0.018 tok/s
  + state decode          0.165        9.1x
  + OMP rows              1.136        6.8x
  + AVX2/dequant-free     1.605        1.41x
  + batch/parallel-if     1.655        1.03x
  + GPU dense resident    3.312        2.0x
  + GPU experts 26/40     3.824        1.15x
  + stream rump + thread  **5.672**    1.48x    (~0.19s/token flat; prefill 0.96s)
  CUMULATIVE                          **315x**

PROFILE (0.19s/step): moe 82% — of which resident ~20ms, STREAMED ~10ms/layer x15
(pageable-mmap H2D at ~1-2GB/s effective is the cost); conv+recur 0.11s/9steps; everything
else near-zero. GPU-4 (pre-scoped): (a) PINNED double-buffered staging for streamed slices
(overlap copy with compute; est ~2x on the stream cost -> ~10-11 tok/s ceiling); (b) expert
LRU IF routing locality is high (instrument hit-rates first); (c) on-device argmax + resident
logits; (d) then wire the whole thing into a served daemon path (the real deliverable).
ENV: engine + submodule this-commit; 25/40 resident at QWEN36_GPU_MOE_GB=9.7 + slab;
QWEN36_GPU_STREAM=1. Raw: _gen_gpu3.out, _prof5.err.
